g.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1224, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0268423508540931e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a defense researcherwho\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"militant groups\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"act\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1212}, {\"ngram\": \"a stark warning\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Terrorist groups have long earmarked rail systems as a stage for attacks ranging from \\\"spectaculars\\\" - that is, coordinated, simultaneous acts designed to cause maximum amount of disruption, harm and panic - to lower-level disruptive acts.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Terrorist groups\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"rail systems\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"a stage\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"attacks\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"spectaculars\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \", coordinated, simultaneous acts\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"maximum amount\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1434}, {\"ngram\": \"disruption\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"harm\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"panic\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"lower-level disruptive acts\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1497}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The persistent evolution in extremists' tactics presents a critical challenge to global security, particularly when it comes to public transportation.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1649, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The persistent evolution\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"extremists' tactics\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"a critical challenge\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1576}, {\"ngram\": \"global security\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"public transportation\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rail lines that connect cities around the world remain uniquely vulnerable to threats both old and new.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rail lines\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1664}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"threats\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The attacks in France not only disrupted physical infrastructure, they also instilled widespread fear and uncertainty, especially given that Paris is a city still scarred with thememory of recent terrorist attacks.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1774, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5258945527139479, \"rank\": 0.6407871300977822, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0268423508540931e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The attacks\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"physical infrastructure\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"widespread fear\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1860}, {\"ngram\": \"uncertainty\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1876}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"thememory\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"recent terrorist attacks\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Authorities were quick todescribe the arson attack as \\\"criminal acts\\\" rather than terrorism.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Authorities\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1986}, {\"ngram\": \"the arson attack\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"criminal acts\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2043}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorism\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But they were clearly the result of sophisticated planning and a high degree of coordination.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"sophisticated planning\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2127}, {\"ngram\": \"a high degree\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"coordination\", \"from\": 2149, \"to\": 2161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And aspects of the France attack reflect recent terrorist thinking.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2182, \"end\": 2188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5258945527139479, \"rank\": 0.6407871300977822, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"aspects\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2174}, {\"ngram\": \"recent terrorist thinking\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Dec. 30, 2023, al-Qaidareleased a promotional videofor the upcoming issue of its online magazine Inspire, focusing on train stations as targets.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2379, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dec.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"al-Qaidareleased\", \"from\": 2250, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"its online magazine Inspire\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"train stations\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"targets\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2378}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The propaganda revisits the theme of rail vulnerabilities andencourages methodssuch as arson.\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the theme\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"rail vulnerabilities\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2438}, {\"ngram\": \"methodssuch\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"arson\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2473}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This suggests a strategic shift toward low-tech, high-impact attacks that can be executed by individuals to disrupt daily life on a massive scale.\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strategic shift\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2506}, {\"ngram\": \"low-tech, high-impact attacks\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2543}, {\"ngram\": \"individuals\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"daily life\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2601}, {\"ngram\": \"a massive scale\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2620}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This tactical shift is not just a blueprint for chaos but a psychological strategy designed to instill fear and paralysis in millions of commuters.\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This tactical shift\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"just a blueprint\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2666}, {\"ngram\": \"chaos\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2676}, {\"ngram\": \"a psychological strategy\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2705}, {\"ngram\": \"fear\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2730}, {\"ngram\": \"paralysis\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2744}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 2748, \"to\": 2756}, {\"ngram\": \"commuters\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trains are symbols of routine and reliability.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2818, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Trains\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2778}, {\"ngram\": \"symbols\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"routine\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2801}, {\"ngram\": \"reliability\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An attack on them can shatter that sense of everyday safety and infuse a pervasive atmosphere of fear and vulnerability.\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2939, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An attack\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2828}, {\"ngram\": \"that sense\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"everyday safety\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2878}, {\"ngram\": \"a pervasive atmosphere\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"fear\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2920}, {\"ngram\": \"vulnerability\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Europe, in particular, there are painful memories of such attacks; the2004 Madrid train bombingskilled 192 people and injured over 2,000, and a year later the2005 London bombingson a bus and tube trains resulted in the death of 52 people and injured more than 700.\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 3208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3019, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid\", \"score\": 0.9999992376040787, \"rank\": 7.62339200838851e-07, \"text\": \"Madrid\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madrid\"}, {\"begin\": 3107, \"end\": 3113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999996731294117, \"rank\": 2.3050084408676697e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 2944, \"to\": 2950}, {\"ngram\": \"painful memories\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2993}, {\"ngram\": \"such attacks\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"192 people\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"a bus and tube trains\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"the death\", \"from\": 3159, \"to\": 3168}, {\"ngram\": \"52 people\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The timing and location of the Paris arson attacks - just as the city was gearing up for a global celebration,the Olympic Games- magnify their impact, extending the psychological reach far beyond the immediate physical damage.\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3241, \"end\": 3246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0268423508540931e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The timing\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3220}, {\"ngram\": \"location\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3279}, {\"ngram\": \"a global celebration\", \"from\": 3299, \"to\": 3319}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games-\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3338}, {\"ngram\": \"their impact\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3359}, {\"ngram\": \"the psychological reach\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3394}, {\"ngram\": \"the immediate physical damage\", \"from\": 3406, \"to\": 3435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Theeconomic repercussions can also be dire.\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Theeconomic repercussions\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3463}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The immediate effects include repair costs and heightened security expenditures, but the broader economic disruptions - delays, lost tourism revenue and shaken investor confidence in the region's stability - can linger long after the tracks are cleared.\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The immediate effects\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3503}, {\"ngram\": \"repair costs\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3524}, {\"ngram\": \"heightened security expenditures\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3561}, {\"ngram\": \"the broader economic disruptions - delays\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3608}, {\"ngram\": \"tourism revenue\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3630}, {\"ngram\": \"investor confidence\", \"from\": 3642, \"to\": 3661}, {\"ngram\": \"the region's stability\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"the tracks\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cities like Paris, reliant on their robust public transport systems, face significant economic setbacks from such attacks, which can stifle economic activity and growth.\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3749, \"end\": 3754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0268423508540931e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cities\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"their robust public transport systems\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3804}, {\"ngram\": \"significant economic setbacks\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3840}, {\"ngram\": \"such attacks\", \"from\": 3846, \"to\": 3858}, {\"ngram\": \"economic activity\", \"from\": 3877, \"to\": 3894}, {\"ngram\": \"growth\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3905}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The timing of the Paris incident meant not only local commuters were affected but also international visitors, potentially leading to a ripple effect across the global perception of security in European transport hubs.\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 4125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3925, \"end\": 3930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0268423508540931e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The timing\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3917}, {\"ngram\": \"local commuters\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 3970}, {\"ngram\": \"a ripple effect\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4056}, {\"ngram\": \"the global perception\", \"from\": 4064, \"to\": 4085}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 4089, \"to\": 4097}, {\"ngram\": \"European transport hubs\", \"from\": 4101, \"to\": 4124}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Terrorist groups are well aware of these long-lasting effects of an attack on rail networks - it is a theme that has beenprominently featured in terrorist propaganda.\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4293, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Terrorist groups\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4143}, {\"ngram\": \"these long-lasting effects\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4188}, {\"ngram\": \"an attack\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4201}, {\"ngram\": \"rail networks\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4218}, {\"ngram\": \"a theme\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4234}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorist propaganda\", \"from\": 4272, \"to\": 4292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, the 17th issue of al-Qaida in the Arabian Peninsula'sInspire magazine, released in August 2017, detailed a simple method for derailing trains by placing obstructions on the tracks - a tactic that requires no advanced technical skills, only the resolve to create havoc.\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4326, \"end\": 4334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"al-Qaida\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\"}, {\"begin\": 4342, \"end\": 4359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_states_of_the_Persian_Gulf\", \"score\": 0.9997525341448124, \"rank\": 0.000247527109473237, \"text\": \"Arabian Peninsula\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_states_of_the_Persian_Gulf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_states_of_the_Persian_Gulf\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 4299, \"to\": 4306}, {\"ngram\": \"the 17th issue\", \"from\": 4308, \"to\": 4322}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4397}, {\"ngram\": \"a simple method\", \"from\": 4413, \"to\": 4428}, {\"ngram\": \"trains\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4449}, {\"ngram\": \"obstructions\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4473}, {\"ngram\": \"the tracks\", \"from\": 4477, \"to\": 4487}, {\"ngram\": \"a tactic\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4498}, {\"ngram\": \"no advanced technical skills\", \"from\": 4513, \"to\": 4541}, {\"ngram\": \"only the resolve\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4559}, {\"ngram\": \"havoc\", \"from\": 4570, \"to\": 4575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inspire's strategic insights suggest targeting trains near critical structures such as mountains, buildings, bridges or tunnels to maximize impact, damage and casualties.\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Inspire's strategic insights\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4606}, {\"ngram\": \"trains\", \"from\": 4625, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"critical structures\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4656}, {\"ngram\": \"mountains\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4674}, {\"ngram\": \"buildings\", \"from\": 4676, \"to\": 4685}, {\"ngram\": \"bridges\", \"from\": 4687, \"to\": 4694}, {\"ngram\": \"tunnels\", \"from\": 4698, \"to\": 4705}, {\"ngram\": \"impact\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4724}, {\"ngram\": \"damage\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4732}, {\"ngram\": \"casualties\", \"from\": 4737, \"to\": 4747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The magazine notes that \\\"5.6 million passengers ride the New York subway every day, and in France, 15,000 trains pass through 3,000 stations daily,\\\" highlighting the intent to inspire attacks on densely populated, high-impact targets.\", \"from\": 4749, \"to\": 4983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4806, \"end\": 4821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Subway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New York subway\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Subway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Subway\"}, {\"begin\": 4840, \"end\": 4846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.5258945527139479, \"rank\": 0.6407871300977822, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The magazine\", \"from\": 4749, \"to\": 4761}, {\"ngram\": \"5.6 million passengers\", \"from\": 4774, \"to\": 4796}, {\"ngram\": \"15,000 trains\", \"from\": 4848, \"to\": 4861}, {\"ngram\": \"3,000 stations\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 4889}, {\"ngram\": \"the intent\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4921}, {\"ngram\": \"attacks\", \"from\": 4933, \"to\": 4940}, {\"ngram\": \"densely populated, high-impact targets\", \"from\": 4944, \"to\": 4982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even years after its publication, the August 2017 issue of Inspire has been circulated repeatedly, especially at times of major geopolitical events such as theU.S.\", \"from\": 4985, \"to\": 5148, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its publication\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5017}, {\"ngram\": \"the August 2017 issue\", \"from\": 5019, \"to\": 5040}, {\"ngram\": \"Inspire\", \"from\": 5044, \"to\": 5051}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 5098, \"to\": 5103}, {\"ngram\": \"major geopolitical events\", \"from\": 5107, \"to\": 5132}, {\"ngram\": \"theU.S.\", \"from\": 5141, \"to\": 5148}]}, {\"sentence\": \"withdrawal from Afghanistanand theIsrael-Hamas conflict.\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5205, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"withdrawal\", \"from\": 5149, \"to\": 5159}, {\"ngram\": \"Afghanistanand theIsrael-Hamas conflict\", \"from\": 5165, \"to\": 5204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And al-Qaidacontinues to encouragelone actors to undertake attacks that can disrupt major urban centers, leveraging the widespread accessibility of the proposed methods.\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"And al-Qaidacontinues\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5228}, {\"ngram\": \"actors\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5252}, {\"ngram\": \"attacks\", \"from\": 5266, \"to\": 5273}, {\"ngram\": \"major urban centers\", \"from\": 5291, \"to\": 5310}, {\"ngram\": \"the widespread accessibility\", \"from\": 5323, \"to\": 5351}, {\"ngram\": \"the proposed methods\", \"from\": 5355, \"to\": 5375}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rail networks arean attractive target for terroristsfor several reasons.\", \"from\": 5378, \"to\": 5450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rail networks arean attractive target\", \"from\": 5378, \"to\": 5415}, {\"ngram\": \"several reasons\", \"from\": 5434, \"to\": 5449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are inherently accessible, often lightly secured and can be densely packed.\", \"from\": 5451, \"to\": 5531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The very efficiency and openness that make urban rail systems the lifeblood of a city also render them vulnerable to attacks.\", \"from\": 5532, \"to\": 5657, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The very efficiency\", \"from\": 5532, \"to\": 5551}, {\"ngram\": \"openness\", \"from\": 5556, \"to\": 5564}, {\"ngram\": \"urban rail systems\", \"from\": 5575, \"to\": 5593}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 5611, \"to\": 5617}, {\"ngram\": \"attacks\", \"from\": 5649, \"to\": 5656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, the potential for high casualties and significant media coverage ensures that even a small act can send shock waves of disruption both locally and internationally.\", \"from\": 5659, \"to\": 5836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the potential\", \"from\": 5673, \"to\": 5686}, {\"ngram\": \"high casualties\", \"from\": 5691, \"to\": 5706}, {\"ngram\": \"significant media coverage\", \"from\": 5711, \"to\": 5737}, {\"ngram\": \"even a small act\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5767}, {\"ngram\": \"shock waves\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 5788}, {\"ngram\": \"disruption\", \"from\": 5792, \"to\": 5802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the U.S., the risk of violent extremists' attacks on critical infrastructure remains alarmingly high.\", \"from\": 5838, \"to\": 5942, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5849}, {\"ngram\": \"the risk\", \"from\": 5851, \"to\": 5859}, {\"ngram\": \"violent extremists' attacks\", \"from\": 5863, \"to\": 5890}, {\"ngram\": \"critical infrastructure\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 5917}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From 2016 to 2022, U.S. federal courtscharged 94 individualswith planning violent extremist attacks, 35 of whom specifically targeted critical infrastructure.\", \"from\": 5943, \"to\": 6101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"U.S. federal\", \"from\": 5962, \"to\": 5974}, {\"ngram\": \"94 individualswith planning violent extremist attacks\", \"from\": 5989, \"to\": 6042}, {\"ngram\": \"critical infrastructure\", \"from\": 6077, \"to\": 6100}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, 19 of these individuals were jihadists affiliated with the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria and al-Qaida.\", \"from\": 6102, \"to\": 6215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6170, \"end\": 6183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6368660342606094e-16, \"text\": \"Islamic State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 6196, \"end\": 6201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9983119231072951, \"rank\": 0.0016909313147543791, \"text\": \"Syria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\"}, {\"begin\": 6206, \"end\": 6214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"al-Qaida\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these individuals\", \"from\": 6117, \"to\": 6134}, {\"ngram\": \"jihadists\", \"from\": 6140, \"to\": 6149}, {\"ngram\": \"Iraq\", \"from\": 6187, \"to\": 6191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And of the seven jihadist plots involving transportation, five targeted mass transit and public rail services.\", \"from\": 6216, \"to\": 6326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6233, \"end\": 6241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\", \"score\": 0.9999461887673141, \"rank\": 4.8237354280333103e-05, \"text\": \"jihadist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"transportation\", \"from\": 6258, \"to\": 6272}, {\"ngram\": \"public rail services\", \"from\": 6305, \"to\": 6325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The attacks on Paris' rail lines should serve as a wake-up call.\", \"from\": 6328, \"to\": 6392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6343, \"end\": 6348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0268423508540931e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The attacks\", \"from\": 6328, \"to\": 6339}, {\"ngram\": \"a wake-up call\", \"from\": 6377, \"to\": 6391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The continuous circulation of Inspire magazine's issues and the recent promotional push for al-Qaida's \\\"open source jihad\\\" campaign underscore a grim reality: The terrorist threat is evolving, adapting new forms of low-tech tactics that exploit the vulnerabilities of critical infrastructure such as railways.\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6424, \"end\": 6440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inspire_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9999980574858223, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Inspire magazine\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inspire_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inspire_(magazine)\"}, {\"begin\": 6486, \"end\": 6494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"al-Qaida\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al-Qaeda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The continuous circulation\", \"from\": 6394, \"to\": 6420}, {\"ngram\": \"the recent promotional push\", \"from\": 6454, \"to\": 6481}, {\"ngram\": \"a grim reality\", \"from\": 6537, \"to\": 6551}, {\"ngram\": \"The terrorist threat\", \"from\": 6553, \"to\": 6573}, {\"ngram\": \"new forms\", \"from\": 6596, \"to\": 6605}, {\"ngram\": \"low-tech tactics\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 6625}, {\"ngram\": \"the vulnerabilities\", \"from\": 6639, \"to\": 6658}, {\"ngram\": \"critical infrastructure\", \"from\": 6662, \"to\": 6685}, {\"ngram\": \"railways\", \"from\": 6694, \"to\": 6702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This evolution marks a significant shift in terrorist strategy, moving from spectacular, resource-heavy plots to simpler, more accessible forms of disruption that any individual can execute without formal training or support networks.\", \"from\": 6705, \"to\": 6939, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This evolution\", \"from\": 6705, \"to\": 6719}, {\"ngram\": \"a significant shift\", \"from\": 6726, \"to\": 6745}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorist strategy\", \"from\": 6749, \"to\": 6767}, {\"ngram\": \"spectacular, resource-heavy plots\", \"from\": 6781, \"to\": 6814}, {\"ngram\": \"simpler, more accessible forms\", \"from\": 6818, \"to\": 6848}, {\"ngram\": \"disruption\", \"from\": 6852, \"to\": 6862}, {\"ngram\": \"any individual\", \"from\": 6868, \"to\": 6882}, {\"ngram\": \"formal training\", \"from\": 6903, \"to\": 6918}, {\"ngram\": \"support networks\", \"from\": 6922, \"to\": 6938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The simplicity and low-tech nature of the sabotage methods prescribed in terrorist propaganda make preventing such attacks challenging, but it is a necessary endeavor to ensure the safety of millions who rely on public transportation daily.\", \"from\": 6941, \"to\": 7181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The simplicity and low-tech nature\", \"from\": 6941, \"to\": 6975}, {\"ngram\": \"the sabotage methods\", \"from\": 6979, \"to\": 6999}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorist propaganda\", \"from\": 7014, \"to\": 7034}, {\"ngram\": \"such attacks\", \"from\": 7051, \"to\": 7063}, {\"ngram\": \"a necessary endeavor\", \"from\": 7087, \"to\": 7107}, {\"ngram\": \"the safety\", \"from\": 7118, \"to\": 7128}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 7132, \"to\": 7140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2025,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 7183, \"to\": 7237, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Copyright \\u00a9\", \"from\": 7183, \"to\": 7194}, {\"ngram\": \"Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 7209, \"to\": 7237}]}]}"